A value from the <xref href="System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollectionType"></xref> enumeration representing the type of the collection.
Gets or sets the item at the specified index.

If you set an item at an index where an item already exists, the existing item is removed and the new item is then assigned to its index position in the collection.
The index at which to get or set the item.
The item at the specified index.
Gets the specified item from the collection.
This API is obsolete.

The <xref:System.Web.Mobile.DeviceFilterElementCollection.Item%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property can only get an item.
To set an item, use the <xref:System.Web.Mobile.DeviceFilterElementCollection.Item%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property, which can both set and get an item.
The string that identifies the item.
The specified item in the collection.

This overload gets the key from the object referenced by the `deviceFilter` parameter and then calls the <xref:System.Web.Mobile.DeviceFilterElementCollection.Remove%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method with the key as the argument.
The item to remove from the collection.
Removes an item from the collection at the specified index.
